"use strict";(self.webpackChunkweslley_io=self.webpackChunkweslley_io||[]).push([[2441],{7601:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"route":"talks","tag":"SP","articles":[{"title":"TDC S\xe3o Paulo","slug":"tdc-sao-paulo","date":"2025-09-18","authors":["Weslley Ara\xfajo"],"tags":["BR","SP","S\xe3o Paulo"],"content":"\\n\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Talk:** Uncovering Tests: Creating Secure and Resilient Systems  \\n\ud83e\udd1d **Feat:** [Larissa Azevedo](https://www.linkedin.com/in/larissasazevedo/)\\n\\n:::note Summary\\n\\n- Test the functionality of our application? \u2705\\n- Break our application before the user or an attacker? That\'s different.\\n\\n:::\\n\\n{/* truncate */}\\n\\nLet\'s demystify test coverage and understand how to create tests that make our application predictable against the unpredictable.\\n\\nMore than just testing, you will learn to create secure validations and understand in practice the impact of data transformation.\\n\\nAnd if you think security is just about code, even the LGPD will come through here from the perspective of someone who managed to access our database.\\n\\nThe idea is for you to realize that tests are not an additional task: they are part of our application and are essential for digital and human security.\\n","filePath":"tdc.mdx","mdxPath":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2025/09/18/tdc.mdx","summary":[],"description":"\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Talk:** Uncovering Tests: Creating Secure and Resilient Systems  \\n\ud83e\udd1d **Feat:** [Larissa Azevedo](https://www.linkedin.com/in/larissasazevedo/)\\n\\n:::note Summary\\n\\n- Test the functionality of our application? \u2705\\n- Break our application before the user or an attacker? That\'s different.\\n\\n:::","social":"./banner.jpeg","socialPath":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2025/09/18/banner.jpeg","readingTime":1,"lastModified":"2025-12-20T19:21:33.000Z","authorsData":[{"name":"Weslley Ara\xfajo","title":"Active open-source contributor, Microsoft MVP, MySQL2\'s maintainer and Poku\'s creator \u2728","url":"https://weslley.io/en/","image_url":"/img/avatar.png","socials":{"linkedin":"wellwelwel","github":"wellwelwel","instagram":"wellwelwel","youtube":"weslleyio"}}],"nextArticle":{"title":"Roga DX","slug":"roga-dx","description":"\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Talk:** Uncovering Tests: Creating Secure and Resilient Systems\\n\\n:::note Summary\\n\\n- Test the functionality of our application? \u2705\\n- Break our application before the user or an attacker? That\'s different.\\n\\n:::\\n\\n:::tip Bonus\\n\\nIn addition to the lecture, I had the immense pleasure of recording an episode of the podcast from [**Curso em V\xeddeo**](https://www.youtube.com/cursoemvideo) with, simply, [**Gustavo Guanabara**](https://www.instagram.com/gustavoguanabara/) \ud83d\udd96\\n\\n:::","social":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2025/09/13/banner.jpeg"}},{"title":"Semana de Sistemas de Informa\xe7\xe3o (EACH-USP)","slug":"semana-de-sistemas-de-informacao-each-usp","date":"2025-08-21","authors":["Weslley Ara\xfajo"],"tags":["BR","SP","S\xe3o Paulo"],"content":"\\n\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Keynote:** GitHub Beyond Code: overcoming in the job market through open source\\n\\n:::note\\nSpeaking at a university ([**USP**](https://www5.each.usp.br/)) is special in itself, but closing the day\'s event made it even more special \u2728\\n\\nThe [**SSI**](https://www.semanadesi.com/) is an event organized by the university students themselves, and I had the pleasure of being invited to teach through open source, using **GitHub** as a learning tool.\\n:::\\n\\n{/* truncate */}\\n\\nFocusing on how to stand out in an increasingly competitive market, I show how open source can accelerate your technical growth, enabling you to achieve unimaginable milestones that directly impact your professional career.\\n\\nIn a market that is more competitive every day, open source is not just about code \u2014 it\'s a direct bridge to technical growth, global visibility, and real career opportunities.\\n\\nWith visual, human, and real examples, I want to inspire you and bring an optimistic perspective of yourself in an increasingly intimidating world, especially with the rise of artificial intelligence, using open source strategically to build credibility and trust in the market.\\n","filePath":"each-usp.mdx","mdxPath":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2025/08/21/each-usp.mdx","summary":[],"description":"\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Keynote:** GitHub Beyond Code: overcoming in the job market through open source\\n\\n:::note\\nSpeaking at a university ([**USP**](https://www5.each.usp.br/)) is special in itself, but closing the day\'s event made it even more special \u2728\\n\\nThe [**SSI**](https://www.semanadesi.com/) is an event organized by the university students themselves, and I had the pleasure of being invited to teach through open source, using **GitHub** as a learning tool.\\n:::","social":"./banner.jpeg","socialPath":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2025/08/21/banner.jpeg","readingTime":1,"lastModified":"2025-12-20T19:21:33.000Z","authorsData":[{"name":"Weslley Ara\xfajo","title":"Active open-source contributor, Microsoft MVP, MySQL2\'s maintainer and Poku\'s creator \u2728","url":"https://weslley.io/en/","image_url":"/img/avatar.png","socials":{"linkedin":"wellwelwel","github":"wellwelwel","instagram":"wellwelwel","youtube":"weslleyio"}}],"previousArticle":{"title":"MVP Conf: Tech Talk","slug":"mvp-conf%3A-tech-talk","description":"\ud83d\udcf9 **Palestra (Live):** GitHub Beyond Code: overcoming in the job market through open source\\n\\n:::note Summary\\nAimed at new developers, I spoke about the impact that open source and **GitHub** can have on our careers, on the **TechTalk** program from the [**MVP Conf**](https://www.youtube.com/@mvpconf) channel, hosted by [**Vanessa Valle**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/vanessabrava/) and [**Renata Correa**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/correa-renata-ti/).\\n:::","social":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2025/08/27/banner.png"},"nextArticle":{"title":"DevConverge LATAM & Oracle \u2014 SPRINT SP","slug":"devconverge-latam-%26-oracle-sprint-sp","description":"\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Talk:** Inventing the New: The Meeting Point Between Human Creativity and AI-Assisted Generation\\n\\n:::note Summary\\nImproving performance in a legacy system is part of the routine. Inventing algorithms and a brand-new architecture is something completely different.\\n:::","social":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2025/08/09/banner.jpeg"}},{"title":"DevConverge LATAM & Oracle \u2014 SPRINT SP","slug":"devconverge-latam-%26-oracle-sprint-sp","date":"2025-08-09","authors":["Weslley Ara\xfajo"],"tags":["BR","SP","S\xe3o Paulo"],"content":"\\n\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Talk:** Inventing the New: The Meeting Point Between Human Creativity and AI-Assisted Generation\\n\\n:::note Summary\\nImproving performance in a legacy system is part of the routine. Inventing algorithms and a brand-new architecture is something completely different.\\n:::\\n\\n{/* truncate */}\\n\\nIn this talk, I share the behind-the-scenes of rebuilding a critical open source ecosystem library, **MySQL2**, to efficiently process billions of **MySQL** requests.\\n\\nWe\'ll go through the problems, ideas, implementations, how to teach **LLMs** to handle something new, and even the remediation of 4 large-scale critical vulnerabilities (**CVEs**).\\n\\nAdditionally, you\'ll learn about the process of making the largest **MySQL** client for **JavaScript** compatible with **TypeScript**, **Bun**, **Deno**, and **Cloudflare Workers**.\\n","filePath":"oracle.mdx","mdxPath":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2025/08/09/oracle.mdx","summary":[],"description":"\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Talk:** Inventing the New: The Meeting Point Between Human Creativity and AI-Assisted Generation\\n\\n:::note Summary\\nImproving performance in a legacy system is part of the routine. Inventing algorithms and a brand-new architecture is something completely different.\\n:::","social":"./banner.jpeg","socialPath":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2025/08/09/banner.jpeg","readingTime":1,"lastModified":"2025-12-20T19:21:33.000Z","authorsData":[{"name":"Weslley Ara\xfajo","title":"Active open-source contributor, Microsoft MVP, MySQL2\'s maintainer and Poku\'s creator \u2728","url":"https://weslley.io/en/","image_url":"/img/avatar.png","socials":{"linkedin":"wellwelwel","github":"wellwelwel","instagram":"wellwelwel","youtube":"weslleyio"}}],"previousArticle":{"title":"Semana de Sistemas de Informa\xe7\xe3o (EACH-USP)","slug":"semana-de-sistemas-de-informacao-each-usp","description":"\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Keynote:** GitHub Beyond Code: overcoming in the job market through open source\\n\\n:::note\\nSpeaking at a university ([**USP**](https://www5.each.usp.br/)) is special in itself, but closing the day\'s event made it even more special \u2728\\n\\nThe [**SSI**](https://www.semanadesi.com/) is an event organized by the university students themselves, and I had the pleasure of being invited to teach through open source, using **GitHub** as a learning tool.\\n:::","social":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2025/08/21/banner.jpeg"},"nextArticle":{"title":"Codecon Summit \u2014 Embrace the Hacker Way","slug":"codecon-summit-embrace-the-hacker-way","description":"\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Talk:** Creating a Test Runner: What happens behind the tests?\\n\\n:::note Summary\\nThere\'s a lot of talk about testing, but what\'s it like to create a test runner from scratch?  \\nMore than that: how do you test a test runner?\\n:::","social":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2025/07/19/banner.jpeg"}},{"title":"Microsoft Reactor e NodeBR","slug":"microsoft-reactor-e-nodebr","date":"2024-08-30","authors":["Weslley Ara\xfajo"],"tags":["BR","SP","S\xe3o Paulo","Online"],"content":"\\n\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Talk:** Creating a High-Performance Multi-Platform Test Runner.\\n\\n:::note\\nThe focus of the talk was on the importance of delegating each problem\'s responsibilities using native **Node.js** features.\\n:::\\n\\n{/* truncate */}\\n\\nWith the theme \\"API Like a Boss\\", I had the opportunity to teach using [**Poku**](https://github.com/wellwelwel/poku).\\n\\nInstead of just talking about Poku itself, I also used Poku as an analogy, teaching about subprocesses and the differences between **Node.js**, **Bun**, and **Deno**.\\n\\n:::tip\\n\\n[See the slides used in the talk \ud83d\udc37](https://drive.google.com/file/d/16XxIt_pov5aBidGjIwC4V_riYq3PMlrB/view)\\n\\n:::\\n","filePath":"microsoft-reactor-e-nodebr.mdx","mdxPath":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2024/08/30/microsoft-reactor-e-nodebr.mdx","summary":[],"description":"\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Talk:** Creating a High-Performance Multi-Platform Test Runner.\\n\\n:::note\\nThe focus of the talk was on the importance of delegating each problem\'s responsibilities using native **Node.js** features.\\n:::","social":"./banner.jpeg","socialPath":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2024/08/30/banner.jpeg","readingTime":1,"lastModified":"2025-12-20T19:21:33.000Z","authorsData":[{"name":"Weslley Ara\xfajo","title":"Active open-source contributor, Microsoft MVP, MySQL2\'s maintainer and Poku\'s creator \u2728","url":"https://weslley.io/en/","image_url":"/img/avatar.png","socials":{"linkedin":"wellwelwel","github":"wellwelwel","instagram":"wellwelwel","youtube":"weslleyio"}}],"previousArticle":{"title":"DevFest Cerrado (Google Developer Groups \u2014 GDG)","slug":"devfest-cerrado-google-developer-groups-gdg","description":"\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Talk:** Overcoming the impostor syndrome and the challenges of existing in the industry through open-source.\\n\\n:::note Summary\\nAt a time when many developers feel insecure about the future of the field, bringing up sensitive topics like insecurity, inferiority complex, and self-sabotage, with a light at the end of the tunnel through open source initiatives, was quite challenging but very interesting:\\n:::","social":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2024/11/23/banner.png"}}]}')}}]);